      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REAL BONNIE (1) is progressing well with another good run last time, placing (29.90) from Box 7 at Gosford. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Deserves serious consideration. JASPER DARKE (2) was well fancied in betting last start but could only manage 2.5 lengths away in third (22.93). Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Nicely placed to grab a well-deserved win. MOLLY MISS (6) is a handy type who was well below best latest at Gunnedah, finishing seventh (30.87) in a NG. Generally a good beginner but was buried in the ruck off the inside last time. Speedy beginner who can find the front despite the tricky draw. Has ability and can measure up. CESSNOCK CURTAIN (4) returns here as an each-way chance.",
